<span id="fn_889"></span>[197:5](sbe31023.htm#fr_892.md) 'Men and herds?'

<span id="fn_890"></span>[197:6](sbe31023.htm#fr_893.md) 'Well-grown.'

<span id="fn_891"></span>[198:1](sbe31023.htm#fr_894.md) I should say that
the suffix has this force here as in close connection with ashyô.

<span id="fn_892"></span>[198:2](sbe31023.htm#fr_895.md) Genius of
rectitude.

<span id="fn_893"></span>[198:3](sbe31023.htm#fr_896.md) Rectitude in
another form.

<span id="fn_894"></span>[198:4](sbe31023.htm#fr_897.md) Literally, 'to the
