may have meant 'seize' originally.

<span id="fn_907"></span>[200:5](sbe31023.htm#fr_910) Ereth*e* (*ri*ti?.md)
seems without inflection.

<span id="fn_908"></span>[200:6](sbe31023.htm#fr_911.md) The state of
activity (?).

<span id="fn_909"></span>[200:7](sbe31023.htm#fr_912.md) Shall we say, 'of
the departed saint' here?

<span id="fn_910"></span>[200:8](sbe31023.htm#fr_913.md) The Pahlavi with
its afkhvâr points here perhaps to a better text. Recall awzhdâtem*k*a,
awzhd*a*unghô, awrem.

<span id="fn_911"></span>[201:1](sbe31023.htm#fr_914.md) Meaning 'without
